rComments: Great professor, easy to do well on exams if you pay attention. Watching recordings instead of attending won't hurt your understanding or grade.

Make sure to watch lectures and fill in gaps with what you dont understand by reading the textbook! Her voice is a bit slow and monotone but overall, I learned a lot and quite enjoyed her class. She responded to my questions quickly via email. She seems like a nice lady

Super solid prof, I have no complaints. The class had lots of assignments throughout but it helped me stay on top of everything. Textbook + sapling aren't needed to do well in the class. Overall, not too difficult of a class, it's basically an intro to organismal bio 2, and Dr. Brennan is a likeable prof

Dr Brennan is the best biology professor I've had at UOttawa. Her lectures are detailed and engaging, and all the examples and diagrams can be found in the textbook. All her assignments, quizzes and midterms were very fair and reflected lecture material well. Always willing to answer questions and very accessible via email.
